  m_Name: Pes_Distal_Phalanx_D2_R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Pes_Distal_Phalanx_D2_R
  partName: Pes Distal Phalanx D2 Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right distal phalanx of the second hind digit forms the terminal bone supporting
    the claw within the canine hindpaw. This structure provides attachment points
    for tendons controlling toe movement and contributes to traction, balance, and
    coordinated locomotion.
  - The distal phalanx also protects sensitive tissues associated with the claw while
    assisting with force distribution during walking and running. Proper alignment
    and integrity are essential for stable digital mechanics and efficient paw function.
